SI prefix - The International System of Units specifies a set of unit prefixes known as SI prefixes or metric prefixes.
SI - The International System of Units (abbreviated SI from Le Système international d'unités) is the modern form of the metric system.
A decimetre (American spelling: decimeter, symbol dm) is a unit of length in the metric system, equal to one tenth of a metre, (or ten centimetres) the SI base unit of length.

Metric system - The metric system is an internationally agreed decimal system of measurement that was originally based on the mètre des Archives and the kilogramme des Archives introduced by France in 1799.
Conversion of units, for comparison with other units of length.
deci- - Deci is a prefix in the metric system denoting a factor of one tenth.
